    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix cqi2hex() function to process all 32 bits of input\n\n### Summary\nThe `cqi2hex()` function in `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/uci_tools_ue.c` was not processing all 32 bits of its input. It was only handling the first 26 bits, missing bits 26-31. This caused incorrect hex representation for CQI values that use the full 32-bit range.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/uci_tools_ue.c`: Added missing terms to process bits 26-31 in the cqi2hex() function\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `cqi2hex()` with input values that have bits set in positions 26-31 (e.g., values >= 0x4000000), the returned value would be incorrect as those bits were being ignored. This could be observed in CQI printouts where high-value CQI reports would show incomplete hex representations.\n\nThe function now correctly processes all 32 bits of the input, converting each 2-bit group into its own nibble in the output for proper hexadecimal display.\n"
}